{
  "page": "Seven Swords",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Seven Swords</b> is the largest inn in <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>. It is a four story structure that towers over the other buildings. Named after the seven members of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">House Darklyn</a> who served in the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, its sign has seven wooden <a href=\"/index.php/Sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sword\">swords</a> painted white. It has a common room. Among some of the fare served at the Seven Swords is bread, hot crab stew, and <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seven_Swords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seven_Swords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>As the <a href=\"/index.php/Captain%27s_sister\" title=\"Captain&#39;s sister\">captain's sister</a> is repainting her oaken shield, <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a> decides to stay overnight in the Seven Swords. She is given a room on the second floor. A <a href=\"/index.php/Darke_(Seven_Swords)\" title=\"Darke (Seven Swords)\">woman with a liver colored birthmark on her face</a> helps her with her bath. Brienne asks her about the <a href=\"/index.php/Darklyn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Darklyn\">Darklyns</a>, and the woman tells Brienne that the lordly Darklyns are all gone. \n</p><p>After her bath, Brienne walks to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dun_Fort\" title=\"Dun Fort\">Dun Fort</a> to speak to the lord. She returns to the Seven Swords's common room for dinner, finding it crowded, but a <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf_brother\" title=\"Dwarf brother\">dwarf brother</a> lets her have his seat. She tells the brother of her quest to find <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">her sister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Dontos_Hollard\" title=\"Dontos Hollard\">a fool</a>, and he tells her that he overheard a man called <a href=\"/index.php/Nimble_Dick\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nimble Dick\">Nimble Dick</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">Maidenpool</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Stinking_Goose\" title=\"Stinking Goose\">Stinking Goose</a> bragging that he had \"fooled a <a href=\"/index.php/Fool\" title=\"Fool\">fool</a>\" seeking passage for three across the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_Sea\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Narrow Sea\">narrow Sea</a>. By the time the common room empties, most of the talk turns to the recent death of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> and who will rule until Tommen comes of age. When the innkeep spits into the fire at the mention of the oathbreaker <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> ruling, Brienne gets up and leaves.  \n</p><p>The next day, Brienne is drinking a breakfast of milk and honey mixed with three raw eggs in the inn's common room when the captain's sister arrives and delivers the repainted shield. Afterwards, Brienne departs the Seven Swords and heads to Maidenpool in search of Nimble Dick.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Seven_Swords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_9\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 9\">Chapter 9</a>, Brienne II.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403092703\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.011 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.012 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 146/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8576/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 716/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 34/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 800/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    6.626      1 -total\n 73.49%    4.8